plainTextMessage.value: FOCS stands for Faculty of Computing and Information Technology. The FOCS of Tunku Abdul Rahman University of Management and Technology (TAR UMT) continuously aims to produce good quality and highly-demanded computing graduates. The good track of records in producing successful digital tech graduates is recognized by the Malaysia Digital Economy Corporation (MDEC) as the preferred digital tech education provider and thereby awarded TAR UMT as one of the Premier Digital Tech Institutions in the presence of the Ministry of Education. View https://www.tarc.edu.my/focs/about-us/ for more information.

FOCS stands for Faculty of Computing and Information Technology. FOCS actively involves in industry based research and development projects that require the latest knowledge and skills in the area of Artificial Intelligence, Data Science, Big Data Analytics, Machine Learning and Internet of Things to prepare our graduates for the Industrial Revolution 4.0 job market as well as readiness for the digital transformation in the industry. View https://www.tarc.edu.my/focs/about-us/ for more information.
